# Paper Mate environment file.
#
# Copy to `.env` (`cp .env.example .env`) and edit. Docker Compose auto-loads
# `.env` from the project root, so these values configure `docker compose up`
# with no extra flags. `.env` is gitignored. All values are optional and fall
# back to the defaults shown below; this file is the canonical list of knobs and
# grows as the project adds configuration.

# --- Storage ---
# Host directory for your library (mounted to /data inside the container, the
# AD-8 storage root). Defaults to the repo-root ./.paper-mate dir (tracked via
# .gitkeep, so it's pre-created on a fresh clone). Uncomment and set this to
# keep your papers/annotations somewhere else instead; pre-create the dir as
# your host user first (the container will not auto-create it).
# PAPER_MATE_DATA=${HOME}/.paper-mate

# --- Networking ---
# Host port the app is published on (the container always listens on 8000).
PAPER_MATE_PORT=8000

# --- Container identity ---
# Host user/group the container runs as, so files written under PAPER_MATE_DATA
# are owned by you (editable/deletable from the host, not root:root). Defaults
# to 1000:1000; override if your host uid/gid differ (check with `id -u` / `id -g`).
PAPER_MATE_UID=1000
PAPER_MATE_GID=1000
